OL,3,CJail for man who fraudulently charged
OL,4,Cpensioner #42,000 for minor garden work
OL,6,FA man fraudulently charged a pensioner
OL,7,Fwith dementia more than #40,000 for
OL,8,Fcarrying out minor work on his garden.
OL,10,FElliot Shaw carried out a number of
OL,11,Fsmall jobs at an 88-year-old man's
OL,12,Fhome over the course of several months
OL,13,Fin 2022.
OL,15,FPolice said it included removing a
OL,16,Fgreenhouse, painting window frames and
OL,17,Ftrimming bushes with all of the work
OL,18,Fcarried out being of a poor standard.
