OL,3,CJail for man who fraudulently charged
OL,4,Cpensioner #42,000 for minor garden work
OL,6,FThe fraud came to light when a member
OL,7,Fof bank staff alerted police after the
OL,8,Fvictim attempted to get a loan to pay
OL,9,FShaw for some of the work.
OL,11,FChecks found that transactions made by
OL,12,Fthe victim matched incoming payments
OL,13,Fto Shaw's bank account.
OL,15,FIt showed that between July and
OL,16,FDecember, Shaw took #42,000 from the
OL,17,Fman, demanding between #500 and #3,000
OL,18,Feach time.
